<subSubSection id="C368652E93508E0DF2AAFC31FCB9FC2A" pageId="9" pageNumber="493" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593508E0DF2AAFC31FCB9FC2A" blockId="9.[151,1437,931,1210]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF893508E0DF2AAFC31FCB5FC2A" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147304" collectorName="J. Serrano" pageId="9" pageNumber="493" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="lectotype">
The specimen here designated as 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793508E0DF033FC31FDA4FC76" box="[526,629,931,957]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">lectotype</typeStatus>
is a male bearing the labels: “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693508E0DF1FBFC36FBC5FC76" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[966,1044,932,957]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incisus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793508E0DF1FBFC36FBC5FC76" box="[966,1044,932,957]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">incisus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
m. in Hispania” and “ 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793508E0DF736FC31FAAFFC76" box="[1291,1406,931,957]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">Lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693508E0DF2AAFC55FDA0FC2A" authority="Dejean, 1829" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[151,625,967,993]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incisus" subGenus="Ophonus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793508E0DF2AAFC55FE04FC2A" box="[151,469,967,993]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">Harpalus (Ophonus) incisus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493508E0DF3E1FC55FDA0FC2A" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[476,625,967,993]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
desig. by 
<collectorName id="2687537393508E0DF0D9FC5AFC8BFC2A" box="[740,858,967,994]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">J. Serrano</collectorName>
”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E93508E0DF2FAFC79FB64FB72" pageId="9" pageNumber="493" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593508E0DF2FAFC79FC0BFB5D" blockId="9.[151,1437,931,1210]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">
Based on the original description, I have selected a beetle from 
<collectingCountry id="F365763593508E0DF1AFFC79FC03FBCE" box="[914,978,1003,1029]" name="Spain" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">Spain</collectingCountry>
as 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793508E0DF1CAFC79FBB3FBCE" box="[1015,1122,1003,1029]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">lectotype</typeStatus>
: 
<emphasis id="B906EAB793508E0DF650FC79FF33FBE2" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">
Il se trouve en 
<collectingCountry id="F365763593508E0DF72EFC7EFAA7FBCE" box="[1299,1398,1004,1029]" name="Spain" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">Espagne</collectingCountry>
, en 
<collectingCountry id="F365763593508E0DF2AAFB9DFF03FBE2" box="[151,210,1039,1065]" name="Italy" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">Italie</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
. This species was treated as a member of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693508E0DF156FB9DFB4AFBE2" authority="Sciaky, 1987" authorityName="Sciaky" authorityYear="1987" box="[875,1179,1039,1065]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Incisophonus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="493" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793508E0DF156FB9DFBD1FBE2" box="[875,1024,1039,1065]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">Incisophonus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493508E0DF634FB9DFB4AFBE2" author="Sciaky, R." box="[1033,1179,1039,1065]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493" pagination="29 - 120" refId="ref12184" refString="Sciaky, R. (1987) Revisione delle specie paleartiche occidentali del genere Ophonus Dejean, 1821. Memoria della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 65, 29 - 120." type="journal article" year="1987">Sciaky, 1987</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
characterized by male protarsomeres notably dilated, aedeagus “aberrant” notably curved to right, elytra notably emarginate apically, etc. (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493508E0DF2A2FBC5FEE5FBBA" author="Sciaky, R." box="[159,308,1111,1137]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493" pagination="29 - 120" refId="ref12184" refString="Sciaky, R. (1987) Revisione delle specie paleartiche occidentali del genere Ophonus Dejean, 1821. Memoria della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 65, 29 - 120." type="journal article" year="1987">Sciaky, 1987</bibRefCitation>
). Additionally, the species is easily identified by a large body size and a cordiform pronotum. Keys to identify it are found in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493508E0DF3A7FBE9FD93FB5E" author="Jeannel, R." box="[410,578,1147,1173]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493" pagination="572 - 1173" refId="ref11231" refString="Jeannel, R. (1942) Coleopteres carabiques. Deuxieme partie. Faune de France 40. Librairie de la Faculte des Sciences, Paris, pp. 572 - 1173." type="book chapter" year="1942">Jeannel (1942)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493508E0DF071FBE9FD2BFB5D" author="Antoine, M." box="[588,762,1147,1174]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493" pagination="315 - 465" refId="ref10238" refString="Antoine, M. (1959) Coleopteres Carabiques du Maroc. Troisieme partie. Memoires de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles et Physiques du Maroc, Nouvelle Serie, Zoologie, 6, 315 - 465." type="journal article" year="1959">Antoine (1959)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493508E0DF13BFBE9FC77FB5E" author="Sciaky, R." box="[774,934,1147,1173]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493" pagination="29 - 120" refId="ref12184" refString="Sciaky, R. (1987) Revisione delle specie paleartiche occidentali del genere Ophonus Dejean, 1821. Memoria della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 65, 29 - 120." type="journal article" year="1987">Sciaky (1987)</bibRefCitation>
, etc.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593508E0DF2FAFB32FB64FB72" blockId="9.[151,1437,931,1210]" box="[199,1205,1183,1210]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">
It is distributed in Mediterranean Europe, 
<collectingCountry id="F365763593508E0DF0A0FB0DFD3CFB72" box="[669,749,1183,1209]" name="Turkey" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">Turkey</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F365763593508E0DF11EFB32FC59FB71" box="[803,904,1184,1210]" name="Morocco" pageId="9" pageNumber="493">Morocco</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493508E0DF1AAFB0DFB78FB72" author="Kataev, B. M. &amp; Wrase, D. W." box="[919,1193,1183,1210]" pageId="9" pageNumber="493" pagination="1810" refId="ref11718" refString="Kataev, B. M. &amp; Wrase, D. W. (2017 c) Subtribe Harpalina Bonelli, 1810. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Lobl, D. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 1. Revised and Updated Edition. Brill, Leiden, pp. 515 - 562." type="book chapter" year="2017">Kataev &amp; Wrase, 2017c</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
